VPC = Virtual Private Cloud
AWS Provides us the public cloud 
Public cloud does not guarantee the security
For security, We create seperate virtual private cloud in a large public cloud hence it gives security as well as isolation.
By default AWS Provides 1 default VPC in each region
VPC Components:
Dividing a large network into small networks = Subnets
--> We create subnets in different Availability Zones (AZs) within a VPC so that we can deploy servers across multiple data centers in a Region. 
--> This improves high availability and fault tolerance because if one Availability Zone becomes unavailable, resources in the other Availability Zones continue to operate.
A subnet consistes of two parts:
1)Public subnet  : 
2)Private subnet 
VPC Architecture: 
"A VPC is a logically isolated virtual network in AWS. We create public and private subnets across multiple Availability Zones for high availability.
Public subnets contain internet-facing resources like Application Load Balancers, Bastion Hosts, and NAT Gateways, while private subnets host application servers and databases.
An Internet Gateway provides internet access to public subnets, and a NAT(Network Access Transaltion) Gateway allows private instances to access the internet for updates without exposing them. 
Security Groups protect instances, and Network ACLs protect subnets."
NAT = It is used to guide to access the Provate subnets through Public Subnets
Internet Gateway --> Public subnets
Internet Gateway --> Public subnets--> NAT Gateway --> Private subnets
Route tables helps us to guide to go to private or public subnets
